<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Parachute — NVC Pitch Deck</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif:ital@0;1&family=DM+Sans:ital,opsz,wght@0,9..40,300;0,9..40,400;0,9..40,500;1,9..40,400&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400&display=swap">
    <style>
        :root {
            --bg:           #faf8f4;
            --bg-soft:      #f3f0ea;
            --fg:           #2c2a26;
            --fg-muted:     #6b6860;
            --fg-dim:       #9a9690;
            --accent:       #4a7c59;
            --accent-soft:  rgba(74, 124, 89, 0.08);
            --border:       #e4e0d8;
            --serif: 'Instrument Serif', Georgia, serif;
            --sans:  'DM Sans', system-ui, sans-serif;
            --mono:  'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
        }

        *, *::before, *::after { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
        html { scroll-behavior: smooth; scroll-snap-type: y mandatory; }

        body {
            background: var(--bg);
            font-family: var(--sans);
            color: var(--fg);
            -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }

        .slide {
            min-height: 100vh;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            justify-content: center;
            padding: 4rem 6rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            scroll-snap-align: start;
            position: relative;
        }
        .slide:last-child { border-bottom: none; }

        .slide-label {
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.14em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }

        .slide-headline {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: clamp(2.8rem, 5.5vw, 4.5rem);
            font-weight: 400;
            letter-spacing: -0.02em;
            line-height: 1.08;
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
        }
        .slide-headline em { font-style: italic; color: var(--fg-muted); }

        .slide-sub {
            font-size: 1.2rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            max-width: 600px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .slide-sub strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Speaker notes -- */
        .speaker-notes {
            display: none;
            margin-top: 2rem;
            padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
            background: var(--bg-soft);
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 8px;
            max-width: 700px;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        .speaker-notes .notes-label {
            font-size: 0.6rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        body.show-notes .speaker-notes { display: block; }

        .notes-toggle {
            position: fixed;
            bottom: 1.5rem;
            right: 1.5rem;
            z-index: 100;
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            background: var(--fg);
            color: var(--bg);
            border: none;
            border-radius: 6px;
            font-family: var(--sans);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            font-weight: 500;
            cursor: pointer;
            opacity: 0.7;
            transition: opacity 0.15s;
        }
        .notes-toggle:hover { opacity: 1; }

        /* -- Stat row -- */
        .stat-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 0;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .stat {
            flex: 1;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .stat:last-child { border-right: none; }
        .stat-num {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 2.5rem;
            color: var(--accent);
            line-height: 1;
            letter-spacing: -0.03em;
            margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
        }
        .stat-label {
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.4;
        }

        /* -- Flywheel -- */
        .flywheel {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            max-width: 500px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
        }
        .fw-step {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.35rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            padding: 0.85rem 0;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.75rem;
        }
        .fw-step:first-child { border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
        .fw-step.final { color: var(--accent); }
        .fw-num {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            width: 1.5rem;
        }

        /* -- Tier table -- */
        .tier-table {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .tier-row {
            display: flex;
            align-items: baseline;
            gap: 1.25rem;
            padding: 0.6rem 1.25rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .tier-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
        .tier-price {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.3rem;
            color: var(--accent);
            min-width: 4.5rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
        }
        .tier-price span { font-family: var(--sans); font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--fg-dim); }
        .tier-body { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
        .tier-body strong { color: var(--fg); font-weight: 500; }
        .tier-highlight { background: var(--accent-soft); }

        /* -- Financial table -- */
        .fin-table {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 600px;
        }
        .fin-table table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
        }
        .fin-table th {
            font-size: 0.65rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            font-weight: 500;
            text-align: center;
            padding: 0.6rem 0.75rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            background: var(--bg-soft);
        }
        .fin-table th:first-child { text-align: left; }
        .fin-table td {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
            text-align: center;
        }
        .fin-table td:first-child {
            font-weight: 500;
            color: var(--fg);
            text-align: left;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
        }
        .fin-table tr:last-child td { border-bottom: none; }
        .fin-table .highlight { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Ask box -- */
        .ask-box {
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            max-width: 500px;
        }
        .ask-row {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: space-between;
            align-items: baseline;
            padding: 0.9rem 1.25rem;
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .ask-row:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
        .ask-row .lbl { font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
        .ask-row .val { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--fg); }

        .close-quote {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3vw, 2rem);
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-top: 2.5rem;
            line-height: 1.3;
            max-width: 550px;
        }
        .close-links {
            margin-top: 1.5rem;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
        }
        .close-links a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
        .close-links a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

        /* -- Architecture diagram -- */
        .arch-diagram {
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
            max-width: 650px;
            padding: 1.5rem 2rem;
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 0;
        }
        .arch-spoke { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
        .arch-spoke-label {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.6rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.1em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
        }
        .arch-spoke.right { align-items: flex-end; }
        .arch-spoke.right .arch-spoke-label { text-align: right; }
        .arch-box {
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 6px;
            padding: 0.4rem 0.9rem;
            font-size: 0.8rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            background: var(--bg);
            white-space: nowrap;
        }
        .arch-hub {
            border: 2px solid var(--accent);
            background: var(--accent-soft);
            color: var(--accent);
            font-weight: 500;
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 1rem 1.25rem;
            text-align: center;
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            line-height: 1.5;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            margin: 0 0.25rem;
        }
        .arch-hub strong { display: block; font-size: 0.95rem; }
        .arch-connector {
            font-family: var(--mono);
            font-size: 0.75rem;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            padding: 0 0.5rem;
            flex-shrink: 0;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.15rem;
        }
        .arch-connector .conn-label {
            font-size: 0.55rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.06em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
        }

        /* -- Competitor landscape -- */
        .landscape {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
            gap: 0;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            overflow: hidden;
            background: #fff;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant {
            padding: 1.25rem;
            border-right: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
        }
        .landscape-quadrant:nth-child(2n) { border-right: none; }
        .landscape-quadrant:nth-child(n+3) { border-bottom: none; }
        .landscape-quadrant .quad-label {
            font-size: 0.55rem;
            letter-spacing: 0.12em;
            text-transform: uppercase;
            color: var(--fg-dim);
            font-weight: 500;
            margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant .quad-names {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.05rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.7;
        }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours { background: var(--accent-soft); }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours .quad-label { color: var(--accent); }
        .landscape-quadrant.ours .quad-names { color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500; }

        /* -- Persona cards -- */
        .persona-row {
            display: flex;
            gap: 1.5rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            max-width: 900px;
        }
        .persona-card {
            flex: 1;
            border: 1px solid var(--border);
            border-radius: 10px;
            padding: 1.5rem;
            background: #fff;
        }
        .persona-card .persona-who {
            font-family: var(--serif);
            font-size: 1.15rem;
            color: var(--fg);
            margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
        }
        .persona-card .persona-how {
            font-size: 0.85rem;
            color: var(--fg-muted);
            line-height: 1.5;
        }

        /* -- Mobile -- */
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .slide { padding: 3rem 1.5rem; }
            .stat-row { flex-direction: column; }
            .stat { border-right: none; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
            .stat:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
            .landscape { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
            .landscape-quadrant { border-right: none !important; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border) !important; }
            .landscape-quadrant:last-child { border-bottom: none !important; }
            .persona-row { flex-direction: column; }
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <!-- Download bar -->
    <div style="position: fixed; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; z-index: 100; background: var(--bg); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 0.75rem 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: space-between;">
        <span style="font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--fg);">Parachute &mdash; NVC Pitch Deck</span>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
            <a href="/nvc/ES_Parachute.pdf" download style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Executive Summary (PDF)</a>
            <a href="/nvc/Parachute.pptx" download style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--accent); color: #fff; border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Pitch Deck (PPTX)</a>
            <a href="/nvc/" style="padding: 0.35rem 0.75rem; background: var(--bg-soft); color: var(--fg); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 5px; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 500;">Full Summary</a>
        </div>
    </div>

    <button class="notes-toggle" onclick="document.body.classList.toggle('show-notes'); this.textContent = document.body.classList.contains('show-notes') ? 'Hide Notes' : 'Speaker Notes';">Speaker Notes</button>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 1 — ASPIRATION                        -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide" style="padding-top: 6rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4rem;">
            <div style="flex: 1;">
                <h2 class="slide-headline">You go for a walk.<br>You talk through your ideas.<br>Your AI <em>already knows.</em></h2>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto;">
                <img src="/nvc/images/pendant-worn.png" alt="Person wearing Parachute pendant outdoors" style="width: 340px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Imagine this: you go for a walk. You talk through what's on your mind &mdash; an idea for a project, a conversation you need to have, something you've been mulling over. By the time you're home, your thoughts are transcribed, organized, and already available to whatever AI you use. You sit down, open Claude or ChatGPT, and it already has the context. It knows what you were thinking about. That's the experience we're building. I'm wearing the device right now. This is Parachute.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 2 — THE RACE                          -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Landscape</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Everyone is building<br>AI agents.</h2>
        <p class="slide-sub">We were too.</p>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            OpenClaw. Claude Cowork. Perplexity Computer. Manus. There are dozens of companies racing to build the best AI agent. Over 100 million people already pay $20+/month for AI. We started here too &mdash; we were building an agentic computing platform, a full AI-powered operating system. But we watched features get cloned in weeks. Every new capability one platform shipped, three others had within a month. It's a race to the bottom, and the big labs have billions of dollars to outspend everyone. So we stopped trying to win that race. And we asked: what's actually missing? What do all of these agents need that none of them are building?
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 3 — THE PROBLEM                       -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">The Problem</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">There&rsquo;s no<br>knowledge layer.</h2>
        <p class="slide-sub">Every AI stores your context as <strong>one flat text file.</strong></p>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Every AI platform &mdash; ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini &mdash; stores your personal context the same way: one big text file. It remembers your name, maybe a few preferences. It doesn't know six months of your thinking. And to give it context, you have to talk to it directly. There's no way to just think for yourself &mdash; on a walk, in the car &mdash; and have that become context your AI can use. The knowledge layer between you and your AI doesn't exist. We're building it.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 4 — THE PRODUCT                       -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 4rem;">
            <div style="flex: 1;">
                <div class="slide-label">The Product</div>
                <h2 class="slide-headline">Parachute Daily.</h2>
                <p class="slide-sub">Voice-first journal. Wearable pendant. Any AI.</p>
            </div>
            <div style="flex: 0 0 auto;">
                <img src="/nvc/images/pendant-render.png" alt="Parachute pendant" style="width: 260px; border-radius: 12px; box-shadow: 0 4px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.08);">
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Parachute Daily is a voice-first journal. You speak into a wearable pendant or your phone &mdash; wherever thinking happens. Your words get transcribed and structured into a personal knowledge graph: notes, tags, and links. Simple for humans, native for AI. The pendant is a wearable voice capture device &mdash; press a button, talk, your thoughts are structured by the time you're home. Working prototype, on stage today.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 5 — HOW IT WORKS                      -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">How It Works</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">Spin up a vault.<br>Give any AI a link.</h2>
        <div class="arch-diagram">
            <div class="arch-spoke">
                <div class="arch-spoke-label">you</div>
                <span class="arch-box">Parachute Daily</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Pendant</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Phone &middot; Web</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-connector">&harr;</div>
            <div class="arch-hub">
                <strong>Parachute Vault</strong>
                Notes &middot; Tags &middot; Links
            </div>
            <div class="arch-connector">
                &harr;
                <span class="conn-label">MCP</span>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-spoke right">
                <div class="arch-spoke-label">your AI</div>
                <span class="arch-box">Claude</span>
                <span class="arch-box">ChatGPT</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Gemini</span>
                <span class="arch-box">Any agent</span>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Your data lives in a Parachute Vault &mdash; a personal knowledge graph organized around notes, tags, and links. It's accessible to any AI via MCP, the open standard Anthropic created for connecting AI to tools. You spin up a vault in seconds and give any AI a link. That's the whole setup. Whatever AI you already use &mdash; Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini &mdash; Parachute makes it better. You don't switch anything. You add Parachute.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 6 — COMPETITIVE LANDSCAPE              -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Competitive Landscape</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">The magic exists.<br>It&rsquo;s not accessible.</h2>
        <div class="landscape" style="max-width: 700px;">
            <div class="landscape-quadrant" style="grid-column: span 2; border-right: none;">
                <div class="quad-label">The proof &mdash; Obsidian + Claude Code</div>
                <div class="quad-names" style="font-size: 1rem;">1M+ users &middot; 8-person team &middot; Bootstrapped &middot; Profitable<br>Power users are already building AI + knowledge graph workflows.<br><span style="color: var(--fg-dim); font-weight: 400;">But it requires markdown, plugins, file systems, and CLI tools. 99% of people won&rsquo;t.</span></div>
            </div>
            <div class="landscape-quadrant">
                <div class="quad-label">Note apps</div>
                <div class="quad-names">Apple Notes<br>Notion</div>
            </div>
            <div class="landscape-quadrant">
                <div class="quad-label">AI platforms</div>
                <div class="quad-names">ChatGPT<br>Gemini<br>Claude</div>
            </div>
            <div class="landscape-quadrant" style="grid-column: span 2; border-right: none; border-bottom: none;">
                <div class="quad-label" style="color: var(--accent);">Parachute &mdash; Obsidian&rsquo;s magic, accessible to everyone</div>
                <div class="quad-names" style="color: var(--accent); font-weight: 500;">Open &middot; Portable &middot; Agent-native &middot; No technical setup</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
            Here's what convinced us this is the right thing to build. Obsidian is a note-taking app &mdash; 8 people, bootstrapped, profitable, over a million users. And a growing community of power users are connecting Obsidian to Claude Code and other AI tools. Give an AI a structured knowledge base and it can work magic. But it requires markdown files, plugin configuration, command-line tools, and file system access. It's incredible for developers and power users. But 99% of people will never do that. On the other side, Apple Notes and Notion have hundreds of millions of users but no AI integration beyond basic features. And the AI platforms themselves &mdash; ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude &mdash; are smart but siloed. Your data is trapped inside their ecosystem. Parachute takes the magic of Obsidian + AI and makes it accessible to everyone. No file system, no CLI, no plugins. Just a vault you spin up in seconds with a link any AI can use. The PKM market is $2.5 billion and growing 16% annually. Obsidian proved the model works with a tiny team. We're building the version that scales to the other 99%.
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <!-- SLIDE 7 — WHO USES THIS                     -->
    <!-- ============================================ -->
    <section class="slide">
        <div class="slide-label">Who Uses This</div>
        <h2 class="slide-headline">For anyone who thinks.</h2>
        <div class="persona-row">
            <div class="persona-card">
                <div class="persona-who">The Thinker</div>
                <div class="persona-how">Morning walk. Talk through ideas. AI already knows yesterday.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="persona-card">
                <div class="persona-who">The Professional</div>
                <div class="persona-how">Voice-notes after meetings. Months of context, any tool.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="persona-card">
                <div class="persona-who">The Enterprise</div>
                <div class="persona-how">Knowledge transfer. Expertise lives on in a vault.</div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="speaker-notes">
            <div class="notes-label">Speaker Notes</div>
